ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Coping Power Integrative Data Analysis (R01MH124438) Original Study Descriptor
Coping Power Integrative Data Analysis post-harmonization School-as-Usual (control) condition
Coping Power Integrative Data Analysis post-harmonization Standard Coping Power condition
Notes: 0 = Not Standard Coping Power; 1 = Standard Coping Power

ElementDescription: Coping Power Integrative Data Analysis post-harmonization Individual Coping Power condition
Notes: 0 = Not Individual Coping Power; 1 = Individual Coping Power

Notes: 0 = Not Teacher-Delivered Coping Power; 1 = Teacher-Delivered Coping Power

ElementDescription: Coping Power Integrative Data Analysis post-harmonization Optimized Coping Power condition
Notes: 0 = Not Optimized Coping Power; 1 = Optimized Coping Power
